List local WASM files in the current directory

Usage: wasm local list [OPTIONS] [PATH]

Arguments:
  [PATH]
          Directory to search for WASM files (defaults to current directory)
          
          [default: .]

Options:
      --hidden
          Include hidden files and directories

      --follow-links
          Follow symbolic links

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version

Global Options:
      --color <WHEN>
          When to use colored output.
          
          Can also be controlled via environment variables: - NO_COLOR=1 (disables color) - CLICOLOR=0 (disables color) - CLICOLOR_FORCE=1 (forces color)
          
          [default: auto]
          [possible values: auto, always, never]

      --offline
          Run in offline mode.
          
          Disables all network operations. Commands that require network access will fail with an error. Local-only commands will continue to work.
